{
  "stem": "7094.5",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe too submissive, but this was the conditioning of a generation and generation.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I saw my grandmother in that situation, these innocent people being subjected to this kind-- I didn't know what was going to happen, but just this stage, you know, with the three days without food and this kind of situation, without any sanitation.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And also, I just couldn't believe that there could be a god who could see all that and-- and allow it to happen.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I just-- I just-- it never occurred to me before.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I never questioned it, because, I say, I was brought up in a very-- but gradually, gradually, I just find-- I mean, religion should have a beneficial-- should-- should do-- give the people a moral code, an ethical.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it can do that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But at the same time, if you see what happened in the name of religion, you begin to doubt it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, all the anti-Semitism which-- Hitler succeeded because he was on fertile ground.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He had this element there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the origin of this anti-Semitic feeling comes from Catholic preaching, from Catholicism.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was made responsible for crucifixion of Christ, even as a child in school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "At Easter time, I was afraid to go out in the street, because I was made responsible for the crucifixion.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They'd forgotten that Jesus was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So-- so-- so you just realize, you know, that religion can have a very beneficial.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It needed it, you know, to-- it can have a very good effect.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But also, what has been done in the name of religion is-- is very-- very catastrophic, too.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
